                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.01/12–1244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-12T00:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 12, 1944—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received December 12—8:32
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4795. ReEmbs 4777, December 11, 10 p.m.<note n="25" xml:id="d1315fn25">Not
                        printed.</note> The French Minister<note n="26" xml:id="d1315fn26">Roger
                        Garreau.</note> yesterday informed me that Stalin had told de Gaulle that
                    the Polish Lublin Committee would shortly declare itself the Provisional
                    Government of Poland. I assume that the Soviet Government will, of course, then
                    recognize them as such. I have received no information on this from the Soviet
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
